113","1089":"1089","after 1140":"na 1140","1087":"1087","1140":"1140","1109":"1109","Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire East Riding, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Anlaby ,Kirk Ella,East Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Kirk Ella, Yorkshire, England","of Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1113–after 1140":"1113–after 1140","1113–1140":"1113–1140","1109–Male":"1109–Deceased","1140–Male":"1140–Deceased","1087–Male":"1087–Deceased","1089–Female":"1089–Deceased","1139":"1139","Abt 1140":"about 1140","1113":"1113","1089":"1089","after 1140":"after 1140","1087":"1087","1140":"1140","1109":"1109","Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire East Riding, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Anlaby ,Kirk Ella,East Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Kirk Ella, Yorkshire, England","of Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hotham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (East Yorkshire): habitational name usually from Hotham (East Yorkshire), but occasionally perhaps also from Holtham in Legsby (Lincolnshire). The East Yorkshire placename may derive from Old English <i>hōdum</i>, dative plural form of <i>hōd</i> ‘shelter’, while the origin of the Lincolnshire placename is uncertain. Compare   Holtham  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Holtham","meanings":["English:","habitational name from a place so named or a topographic name for someone who lived ‘(at the) enclosure in the wood’, from Middle English <i>holt</i> ‘wood, grove’ + <i>ham</i> ‘enclosure’ (Old English <i>holt</i> + <i>hamm</i>). Compare   Haltom   and   Holtom  .","variant of   Hotham  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Hotham was born in 1113, in Kirk Ella, Yorkshire, England, her father, John Hotham, was 26 and her mother, Winifred Bruce, was 24. She married Robert Legard in 1139, in Anlaby, Yorkshire East Riding, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1140, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1113–after 1140":"1113–pärast 1140","1113–1140":"1113–1140","1109–Male":"1109–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1087–Male":"1087–Surnud","1089–Female":"1089–Surnud","1139":"1139","Abt 1140":"umbes 1140","1113":"1113","1089":"1089","after 1140":"pärast 1140","1087":"1087","1140":"1140","1109":"1109","Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire East Riding, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Anlaby ,Kirk Ella,East Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Kirk Ella, Yorkshire, England","of Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1113–after 1140":"1113–1140 jälkeen","1113–1140":"1113–1140","1109–Male":"1109–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1087–Male":"1087–Kuollut","1089–Female":"1089–Kuollut","1139":"1139","Abt 1140":"noin 1140","1113":"1113","1089":"1089","after 1140":"1140 jälkeen","1087":"1087","1140":"1140","1109":"1109","Anlaby, Yorkshire, England":"Anlaby, Yorkshire East Riding, Englanti, Y